<%#
  CZID-286 — Layer 3 device / location attestation step-up page (SERVER-SIDE gate; CLIENT SDK HELD).

  ⚠️ TODO(counsel): copy is a PLACEHOLDER with legal weight — counsel-owned. Precise-location collection is
  sensitive PII and requires consent + a DPA (design doc §10 item 7).

  ⚠️ TODO(vendor) — CLIENT SDK INTEGRATION POINT (HELD): this page is where the device-location vendor's
  frontend SDK (e.g. GeoComply PinPoint web SDK) is embedded. The SDK collects a signed device-attestation
  token and POSTs it to `device_location_attestations_path` as `attestation_token`; the server verifies it
  (see DeviceLocationAttestationsController#create → ExportControl::DeviceLocationProvider). Building that
  vendor-specific frontend against an unknown SDK is deliberately HELD (standing rule) — the form below is
  a documented placeholder so the fail-closed server verifier is exercisable now (an empty/absent token is
  verified server-side and DENIED, which is the correct dark-mode behavior).
%>
<div class="device-location-attestation" style="max-width: 720px; margin: 64px auto; padding: 0 24px; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;">
  <h1 style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
    <%# TODO(counsel): heading copy %>
    Device location verification required
  </h1>

  <div style="background:#f6f8fa; border:1px solid #d0d7de; border-radius:6px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:24px; line-height:1.6;">
    <p><strong>PLACEHOLDER — pending counsel-approved text (TODO(counsel)).</strong></p>
    <p>
      For the most sensitive export-controlled functions, this service verifies your device's real location
      to prevent location spoofing. [Consent language, the vendor identity, and what is collected are
      counsel-owned and will replace this placeholder before enforcement is enabled.]
    </p>
  </div>

  <%= form_with url: device_location_attestations_path, method: :post, local: true do %>
    <p style="color:#57606a; font-size:13px; margin-bottom:20px;">
      Policy version: <%= @attestation_policy_version %> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Provider: <%= @device_provider %>
    </p>

    <%#
      TODO(vendor): the chosen SDK writes the signed device-attestation token into this hidden field before
      submit. With no SDK wired, it stays empty → the server verifier fails closed (DENY).
    %>
    <input type="hidden" name="attestation_token" value="" />

    <button type="submit"
            style="background:#0969da; color:#fff; border:none; border-radius:6px; padding:10px 20px; font-size:15px; cursor:pointer;">
      <%# TODO(counsel): button label %>
      Verify device location
    </button>
  <% end %>
</div>
